description: Archie Meets Archie?! What's going on here?! Seems like something strange is happening in Riverdale, and the gang is meeting up with past versions of themselves! It's causing some trouble, too -- can Jughead out-eat himself? Which Reggie plays the best pranks? And with two Bettys and two Veronicas wandering around, Archie has TWICE the girl trouble!
name: Archie & Friends Blast To the Past

description: The holidays make the gang from Riverdale want to sing, and they want you to come along! Join Archie, Betty, Jughead and the gang on a caroling trip through town. This digital-only collection is pitch perfect as a gift for your friends or loved ones!
name: Archie's Christmas Carols

description: Some think the magic of Christmas is just a saying, but Jingles the Christmas Elf and Sugarplum the Fairy would beg to differ! When these troublemaking sprites show up, you know that Christmas is right around the corner -- and so is mayhem! They're always eager to help Archie and the gang with their holiday problems, but sometimes they do more harm than good! Can they save Christmas from themselves?
name: Archie & Friends The Magic of Christmas

description: Celebrate the 75th anniversary of Archie Comics with this special retrospective presentation! Kevin Keller, introduced in 2010, made a huge splash as he became Riverdale's first openly gay resident. In this installment, we share some of the best and most pivotal stories from his series, from his first issue to his first kiss!
name: Kevin Keller

description: Celebrate the 75th anniversary of Archie Comics with this special retrospective presentation! Archie's rival, Reggie, got his own book at the tail end of the 1940s. For over 120 issues, he caused mischief for his fellow Riverdale High students in the most hilarious ways possible! We'll take a look back at some of that series' best stories and craziest pranks. Will this class clown have the last laugh?
name: Reggie and Me

Heading back to Brosha, Sekken and Iyo meet up with their guild, Emerald Moon. Reunions are cut short as a new crisis emerges that has the means to threaten the entire world. With little time to spare, they depart for Preminx...in hopes of heading off the Dark Legion. With Emerald Moon standing between two armies, it is their hope the Region of Preminx will not be soaked in blood.

Where else in the printed world can you get this much variety for such a small outlay? 48 pages for only $.99 and a wraparound cover by artist Steven Austin. It would be an insult to all of creation to ask for less!

Ah... I Should Explain Why I Was Naked First!

Eden's best friend Erin has finally scored her big break as a stand-up comedian. Eden, Eric and Dice go and check out her first ever live gig. The night isn't without drama though, and it seems that a spell of bad luck has fallen on both Eric and Eden... It's nothing to be worried about, or is it?
name: Ah... I Should Explain Why I Was Naked First!

description:
That Doesn't Sound Good

Eric's disappearance has Eden and Dice worried. Eden asks Alvin and McMahon for their help. They know where he is, but the truth is rather unbelievable, and something that only they can deal with. Eric, in an unfamiliar and helpless situation, takes time to remember days past. How did Eric and Dice first meet?
name: That Doesn't Sound Good

description:
Call Me Tomorrow If You're Still Alive

Eric returns safe and sound, but not before Eden enlists Erin to make a public appeal for information on national TV. In trouble in more ways than one, Eden agrees to Erin's demand to help smooth things over. At home, Eric's time away has placed a seed of doubt in his mind as to Dice's real intentions. Someone is hiding a secret... but who?
name: Call Me Tomorrow If You're Still Alive

description:
The Peril of the Sparklepires

Little-girl paranormal investigator, Rainbow Sprinkle-Slime, has a new case! She's tracking down a mysterious sparklepire, or is she? Join Rainbow in this crazy camping caper.
name: The Peril of the Sparklepires

description:
The Spooky Store of Soda Phantoms

What a way to wake up in the morning! Rainbow's dad gets her out of bed with the startling news that she's been hired to investigate the mysterious haunting of a convenience store by spooky, soda-sipping spectres. Will Rainbow be able to solve this complicated, carbonated caper?
name: The Spooky Store of Soda Phantoms

description:
Rainbow Sprinkle-Slime and the Paranormal Puppy Pest Problem

The local toy store is in a shambles! Can Rainbow Sprinkle-Slime figure out how to deal with the pesky paranormal puppy pest that is causing all the pandemonium? Or will the devilish doggie devour all the dollies? The only way to find the answer to these and other questions you never asked is to read this comic!
name: Rainbow Sprinkle-Slime and the Paranormal Puppy Pest Problem

description: In ancient Japan, ogres and humans live together with a tacit understanding to stay out of each other's affairs.
In ancient Japan, ogres and humans live together with a tacit understanding to stay out of each other's affairs.

Unpacking, Book One

Shirtlifter is a series of queer-themed short fiction comics from artist Steve MacIsaac. The third issue of this award-winning series collects the first three chapters of MacIsaac's online serial "Unpacking", about the development of a relationship between a committment-phobic graphic designer and a corporate executive who isn't quite everything he seems. This third volume also features contributions from Justin Hall (Hard to Swallow) and a new cartoonist named Fuzzbelly. Hall's contribution is an excerpt from his upcoming graphic novel The Liar, while Fuzzbelly's is an autobiographical rumination on eroticism.
name: Unpacking, Book One

description:
Unpacking, Book Two

The fourth issue of Steve MacIsaac's "Shirtlifter" contains another standalone episode of "Unpacking", MacIsaac's graphic novel in progress, which he began in issue three. Matt is a Vancouver graphic designer who has begun spending time with a visiting businessman. The catch? The businessman is straight. And married. And their no strings relationship begins to get tangled.

This issue also features an excerpt from "The Liar" by Justin Hall (Glamazonia, Hard to Swallow) and selection of "Dick" strips from Ilya (End of the Century Club). The digital edition contains 12 pages of bonus materials giving readers a look behind the scenes in the creation of "Unpacking".
name: Unpacking, Book Two

description:
Unpacking, Book Three

This issue, the first in four years, concludes Steve MacIsaac's "Unpacking" graphic novel. Starting in Shirtlifter #3, "Unpacking" follows Matt, a gay graphic designer living in Vancouver. Newly-single after the sudden dissolution of an eight-year relationship, Matt is living in a new apartment he can't seem to quite move into, and is wary of becoming involved with anyone ever again. His commitment to remaining single is challenged when he begins spending time with Connor, an Australian-ex pat who identifies as straight, is married to a woman, and seems to be the only person capable of cutting through Matt's defenses.

Also features new stories from Jon Macy and Eric Kostiuk Williams.
name: Unpacking, Book Three

description:
Pain and Compromises

The Earl Hadge confronts his chamberlain over the rescue of his young rival for the throne of Lifdell, and the difficult circumstances that have risen now that the prince is in the company of the powerful and respected Ravenwood cousins. Meanwhile, Ravenwood chases after the runaway Christian who refuses to return with Cromwell back to Lifdell, learning that a privileged life isn't always a life of luxury, even for a child. And a team of surviving Trolls work their way back to their homeland with the Rats in close pursuit.
name: Pain and Compromises
